I was surprised by how much the state provides for city functions in the larger cities, which contributes to the growth of the state budget. Last night, I saw on TV how ADG&G was showing children how to ice fish - couldn't their parents do that? Yes, I pay property taxes, but I guarantee that once city folks receive the full bill without state funding, we won't be as wasteful. For example, on the office building, rent the space you need and help the office rental market. In my business, I used to ask my managers, "How do you stop spending money?"
